@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "My Hobby: Fortnite";
}

<div class="site-hero text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4 gradient-text">My Hobby: Fortnite</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle mx-auto">
        I play Fortnite because it is fun. I am not amazing at it. I am not trying to go pro.
        I just enjoy the chaos, the vibes, and the occasional accidental win.
    </p>

    <div class="hero-cta d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap gap-3 mt-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary px-4" href="/Home/Pricing">Book Some Tutoring</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost px-4" href="#favorite-skin">Jump To Favorite Skin</a>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
        <div class="page-card">
            <span class="card-tag">Vibes Report</span>
            <h2 class="h4">Why I like playing Fortnite</h2>
            <p>
                Fortnite is my favorite kind of game because it never takes itself too seriously.
                Every match feels different. Sometimes I have a plan. Sometimes I land, panic,
                and immediately start running in the wrong direction.
            </p>
            <p>
                I like the bright art style, the random items, and the fact that winning is never guaranteed.
                Even when I lose badly, it usually happens in a way that is funny enough to make it worth it.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                The best games are always with friends. Even when I am getting carried, I still feel involved
                because Fortnite somehow makes chaos feel collaborative.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="page-card mt-4">
            <span class="card-tag">Strategyâ„¢</span>
            <h2 class="h4">My playstyle (if you can call it that)</h2>
            <p>
                My strategy is very simple: land somewhere calm, collect loot, and then confidently rotate
                directly into danger. When I encounter someone who can build faster than I can think,
                I place exactly one wall and hope for the best.
            </p>
            <p class="mb-0">
                I am fully aware that this is not optimal gameplay. However, it is extremely entertaining,
                and that is the metric I care about the most.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
        <div class="page-card">
            <span class="card-tag">Live Footage</span>
            <h2 class="h5 mb-3">Exhibit A: Peak Fortnite decision-making</h2>

            <img
                src="~/photos/normal_fortnite_playing.png"
                alt="Fortnite gameplay showing a character standing in a colorful outdoor environment"
            />

            <p class="mt-3 mb-0">
                This image perfectly captures my Fortnite experience: standing still, holding a brightly colored item, and staring at something that is clearly not important while danger almost certainly exists somewhere off screen. I feel prepared, confident, and completely unaware of what is about to happen next.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4" id="favorite-skin">
    <div class="page-card">
        <span class="card-tag">Style Flex</span>
        <h2 class="h4">My favorite skin to play as</h2>

        <p>
            My favorite skin to play as is the Sabrina Carpenter skin. Not because it gives me any
            advantage (it does not), but because I think it is genuinely funny when Sabrina Carpenter
            wins a Fortnite match.
        </p>

        <p>
            Seeing a pop star character standing there with a
            <span class="fw-semibold">#1 Victory Royale</span> banner after I spent the entire game
            making questionable decisions feels incredibly undeserved in the best possible way.
        </p>

        <img
            src="~/photos/fortnite-sabrina-carpenter-victory.png"
            alt="Fortnite match ending with a #1 Victory Royale banner while a character resembling Sabrina Carpenter stands holding a weapon"
            class="mt-2"
        />

        <p class="mt-3 mb-0">
            Skins do nothing for gameplay, but this one dramatically improves the emotional impact of winning,
            which is rare enough that it deserves to be memorable.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
    <div class="page-card d-flex flex-column flex-md-row align-items-md-center justify-content-between gap-3">
        <div>
            <h2 class="h5 mb-1">Need help anyway?</h2>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">
                I can help tutor you in Fortnite. My coaching style is encouraging,
                judgment-free, and very realistic.
            </p>
        </div>
        <a class="btn btn-dark" href="/Home/Pricing">Go to tutoring calculator</a>
    </div>
</div>